  "overviewMarkdown": "### Exa-ELDG Hybrid Retrieval Engine v7.0 🧭\n\nExa-ELDG Hybrid v7.0 keeps the strong parts of ELDG-style grounded retrieval—volatility-aware routing, contradiction checks, and machine-legible output—but fixes the major practical gap: not every query wants compressed claims. Some queries need exact artifacts.\n\n#### What changed in v7.0\n1. **Need-class routing now distinguishes facts from artifacts.** The router can classify requests as `fact_pin`, `version_pin`, `tradeoff_map`, `contradiction_audit`, `code_extract`, `verbatim_extract`, `enumeration_extract`, or `procedure_extract`.\n2. **Exact-text and code lanes.** If the query asks for code, clauses, exact quotes, full option sets, or step lists, the output includes dedicated `artifacts` and `structured_items` lanes instead of forcing everything into compressed claim strings.\n3. **Broader first-pass retrieval.** The plugin increases breadth automatically for exhaustive requests so the parent model does not need to issue several near-duplicate follow-up calls just to get enough material.\n4. **Checks and balances remain.** Dynamic or unstable queries can still trigger dual-branch retrieval and contradiction handling rather than blindly trusting a single page.\n5. **Graceful degradation.** If reconciliation fails, the plugin falls back to a source ledger plus evidence lattice rather than returning nothing.\n\n#### Practical guidance for parent LLMs\n- Ask directly for what you need. Example: \"Return the exact TypeScript code snippet for...\" or \"List all route segment config options and allowed values...\"\n- Use `outputIntent: CODE_BOILERPLATE` for code/config extraction and `VERBATIM_STATUTE` for legal/verbatim text.\n- Use `detailMode: EXHAUSTIVE` when you want more breadth on the first pass, or `RAW_TEXT` when exact spans matter more than compression.\n\n#### Setup\n- Enter your Exa API key and Google Gemini API key in the plugin settings.\n- Optionally enter your Cloudflare proxy worker URL. If omitted, the default unified proxy URL is used.\n- Gemini 3.1 Flash-Lite remains the only LLM used inside the plugin for routing and unified reconciliation.\n",
